James de Villiers, News24 This image shows the remains of a vehicle involved in a four-car collision which left two dead and three injured. (Supplied)???? Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; Two people were killed and three injured after four vehicles collided on the R300 in Kuilsriver on Sunday evening, paramdics said.When paramedics arrived on the scene, they found five people trapped inside one one of the vehicles, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said in a statement. Paramedics found that two out of the five people sustained fatal injuries.Three people sustained major injuries. They were taken to the Tygerberg Hospital for further medical attention.&nbsp;The occupants of the three other vehicles sustained no injuries, Meiring said.The cause of the accident is unknown.Local authorities were on scene for further investigation.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.